<div class="forum-post-template-post"> <p>That's a good one.  I'd pretend I was stepping out into the void with no point of reference.  Free falling.  The spark of recognition will send a minor shock throughout the system, especially in the chest region.  I have always taken that to be a good sign--like benefiting from electroshock therapy.  Maybe it takes a lot of those little shocks to change our conditioning, which may be at the heart of our fear of life and the identification we have with life (and thus the fear).  Trimpi</p>
 </div><!-- class="forum-post-template-post" -->
